key_points: A woman claimed on 'Good Morning America' that she gave Brian Laundrie a ride in Wyoming.
She picked Laundrie up on August 29, four days after Gabby Petito's last known call to her family.
Laundrie told the woman, Miranda Baker, he had been camping alone and Gabby Petito was working on their social media.
Laundrie exited Baker's car after learning they were heading to Jackson Hole, quickly disappearing.
The FBI found a body in Grand Teton National Park matching Gabby Petito's description.
The Laundrie family attorney stated that the news about Gabby Petito is heartbreaking and offered prayers.
Brian Laundrie remains missing, last seen by his family in Florida.
Police searches for Laundrie focus on the Carlton Reserve in Sarasota County, Florida.
Police in Moab released a body camera video of an interaction between Gabby Petito and Brian Laundrie.
The interview with Miranda Baker can be viewed on 'Good Morning America'.
